�	Please note that the US government has introduced new guidelines on all flights to the United States. It relates to additional security searches and also restrictions on carrying powder like substances in hand luggage in quantities greater than 12oz or 350ml.  For more information, please visit our travel information tab on our homepage.
�	The US Department of Homeland Security has separate enhanced security screening procedures in place for all commercial flights into the US.  This means that customers travelling to the USA may be subject to questioning by security staff at check-in.  As a result of this, we are unfortunately unable to offer day before check-in for TUI Airways flights at Birmingham, Gatwick and Manchester airports for any customers travelling to Florida.  We have, however, organised dedicated check in areas which will open a minimum of three hours prior to departure for these flights at these airports.
�	Please note, that all hotels in Florida with the exception of the Holiday Inn and Suites and Wyndham Orlando Resort require at least one passenger in each room booked to be over the age of 21.
�	Only guests aged 21 and over are allowed to drive hire cars under Florida law.  If there are no drivers aged 21 or over, the car will be refused on arrival. If this applies to your booking, please select a different transport option instead.
�	Customers who are boarding flights to the US may be requested to have additional checks on their electronic devices � such as phones, laptops, tablets, e-readers, power cables and transformers � by airport security personnel.  For TUI and First Choice, this only affects customers travelling on outbound flights to the US from the UK. If you have any concerns with any of your devices, we would advise that you either leave these items at home or place these items into your hold luggage. Please be aware that batteries and power banks cannot be carried in your hold luggage.
�	For access to up-to-date travel advice, see Travel Aware � Staying Safe and Healthy Abroad.

